{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6063b0e2-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1731a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1731a"},"text":"§ 1731a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Application of subchapter to leases of lands within three miles of seaward boundaries of coastal States","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For fiscal year 1990 and each fiscal year thereafter, notwithstanding the provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s1731"},"text":"section 1731 of this title","children":[],"tail":", sections 1732 through 1736 of this title shall apply to any lease or portion of a lease subject to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1337/g"},"text":"section 1337(g) of title 43","children":[],"tail":", which, for purposes of those provisions and for no other purposes, shall be regarded as within the coastal State or States entitled to receive revenues from it under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1337/g"},"text":"section 1337(g) of title 43","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6063b0e3-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/121/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–121, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-10-23"},"text":"Oct. 23, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/711"},"text":"103 Stat. 711","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6063b0e4-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6063b0e5-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","childre